{"source_key":"sha256-ea08d35f42d5530fbe92c80d4f5b27e9","record_index":583,"record_hash":"sha256:9c27f9ca57bfbb6d8a19665e8f88e0a82b960a9a30959dcba56ca474f4b0d727","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:42:10.038Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: b1bebd\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 901\nOutput:\npackage in Forge rather than importing generated `.node` artifacts directly.\n\nThe helper-binary fallback remains valid when deployment constraints make NAPI\nawkward:\n\n```text\nNext route/API -> TypeScript AgentTrail service -> Rust projection helper JSON\n```\n\nUse that only as a fallback. NAPI avoids a custom stdout/stderr protocol,\nprocess spawning, and binary lifecycle management inside each request.\n\nBuild may start for public repos and publicly fetchable metadata. Private repo,\nteam, explicit-share, and richer publication flows are later work.\n\n## Server-Side Metadata Fetch\n\nFor public v1, the Forge server should be able to create an Agent Trail snapshot\non demand by fetching GitMeta metadata for the repository referenced by the PR\nURL.\n\nThis only works when `refs/meta/main` has actually been published to the public\nGitHub repository. Forge's existing `but-sync` flow pushes metadata to private\ncode.storage workspace refs such as `refs/<client_id>/meta/*`; that does not\nmake metadata available to URL-replacement reviewers. Agent Trail v1 assumes\npublic metadata already exists and should show a missing-metadata state when it\ndoes not. Publishing metadata to GitHub can be a later GitButler/GitMeta\ndistribution feature.\n\nPierre/code.storage should be considered a remote caching and Git hosting layer,\nnot a replacement for local GitMeta materialization in v1. The current\n`git-meta-lib` entry point is path/repository based: `Session::open(path)` opens\na `gix::Repository`, creates or reads `.git/git-meta.sqlite`, fetches/materializes\nmetadata refs into that local store, and reads values through\n`SessionTargetHandle`. `but-agentlog` currently depends on that shape.\n\nThat means Agent Trail still needs a server-side scratch/cache Git repository\nwith filesystem access before calling the NAPI projection API. The NAPI request\nshould pass a local `repoPath`, not raw remote bytes.\n\nPierre does not currently make a remote repository appear as a mounted local\nrepository to the server process. It gives Forge Git hosting/API/proxy\ncapabilities. To make `git-meta-lib` happy, Forge still has to materialize a\nreal local Git repository/object database/ref namespace on disk, even if the\nremote it fetches from is Pierre/code.storage.\n\nPierre may still be useful in front of that local repository:\n\n- If code.storage can import or mirror the public GitHub repository and exact\n  `refs/meta/main`, Forge can fetch the metadata ref from Pierre instead of\n  GitHub.\n- If code.storage can provide a stable Git Smart HTTP remote with better\n  caching/rate-limit behavior, the scratch repo can use that remote for the\n  exact metadata fetch.\n- If Pierre only has Forge's private Cloud workspace refs, those refs are not\n  valid public Agent Trail input for v1.\n\nDo not parse GitMeta trees directly from code.storage file APIs in Forge for\nv1. That would duplicate `git-meta-lib` materialization and `but-agentlog`\nstorage interpretation. A future lower-level `git-meta-lib` API could accept an\nexplicit object database or in-memory GitMeta source, but that is a separate\nlibrary-design project.\n\nIf Forge's deployment target cannot provide a writable cache directory, `git`,\nnative addon loading, and enough request/worker time to fetch and materialize\nGitMeta, do not force Agent Trail generation into this Next.js app. Split the\ngenerator into a separate service or worker with durable local storage and have\nForge call it over HTTP or a queue. Forge can still own the public routes and UI,\nbut the repository cache and projection generation should live where the runtime\nfits the workload.\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:42:10.038Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}